results.name: Highest minimal distance of any Type I (strictly) singly-even binary self-dual code of length 2n.
reference: F. J. MacWilliams and N. J. A. Sloane, The Theory of Error-Correcting Codes, Elsevier/North Holland, 1977.
link: G. Nebe, E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-Dual Codes and Invariant Theory, Springer, Berlin, 2006.
E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-dual codes, pp. 177-294 of Handbook of Coding Theory, Elsevier, 1998; (Abstract, pdf, ps).
example: At length 8 the only strictly Type I self-dual code is {00,11}^4, which has d=2, so a(4) = 2.
xref: Cf. also A105685 for the number of such codes.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 06 2005
ext: The sequence continues: a(28) = either 10 or 12, then a(58) = 10, a(60) through a(68) = 12, ...
